{
  "stem": "17426.3",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 229.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "My father [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] volunteered, and I went with him, to leave my older brother, who was in a position at that point to help my mother and my sister, we thought.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But he too wasn't very long in the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "He too was deported some eight or nine months later.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No good.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "No, there was-- we were so weak, so powerless, so unsupported from the outside, that we had nothing to resist with.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "There were no guns.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "As you know, in Europe, it's not allowed to for private people to have guns, especially at that time.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Now it's perhaps much more liberal, but not those days, and there wasn't a single gun in any Jewish hand.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Jews were not known to be fighters, were not known to-- to threaten with guns or need guns for whatever purpose they are used today for.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So we had really nothing, nothing except hope.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "There was no hospital in Dobra at all.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There was no physician, no medical doctor in Dobra The nearest medical doctor was in Turek, which was some 15, 18 kilometers away from Dobra.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "There was nothing.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "There was a barber, so-called, a [? fetcher, ?] who was a glorified barber that did everything.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "He said [INAUDIBLE], and someone had pneumonia.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And he gave him [?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Baldrian ?] drops when he fainted, and these kind of homespun remedies.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "That's all there was available.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "There was nothing of that kind.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I'm talking about 1941, May of 1941, middle of May.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, I was deported with my father.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "In a sense, I was hopeful that when they put us to work in a labor camp, they will have to support us with food if they want our labor.",
      "word_count": 30
    }
  ],
